{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Wood Monkey|kanji=甲申|romaji=kinoe saru|onyomi=kōshin|p=jiǎshēn|w=chia-shen|mi=ʈ͡ʂja̠²¹ ʂən|y=gaap6 san1|j=gaap6 san1|ci=kaːp̚ ʂɐn|mc=kæp ʂin|oc-bs=kaːp ʔʂin}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Wood Monkey also known as 甲申''' (kinoe saru, kouboku no saru, koushin) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 21st combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Kiboku|ja|癸未}} and followed by {{ill|Otyuu|ja|乙酉}}. In the context of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Monkey|ja|申}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）}}) (i.e. Metal overcomes Wood).

