{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Wood Monkey also known as 甲申''' (kinoe saru, kouboku no saru, koushin) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 21st combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Kiboku|ja|癸未|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Otyuu|ja|乙酉|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the context of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Monkey|ja|申|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|12=draft|12=draft}}) (i.e. Metal overcomes Wood).

==Yang Wood Monkey (甲申)'s Years==
