It is the 21st combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Kiboku|ja|癸未|1=Yin Water Goat|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Otyuu|ja|乙酉|1=Yin Wood Rooster|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the context of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Monkey|ja|申|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) (i.e. Metal overcomes Wood).

